HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES, September 4, 2025.
The committee on Labor and Workforce Development, to whom was
referred the petition (accompanied by bill, House, No. 2075) of Tackey
Chan for legislation to require that certain construction industry employers
provide occupational safety and health administration training to
employees, reports recommending that the accompanying bill (House, No.
4448) ought to pass.
